## **Case Guide ⚙️**

## **Case Priority**

1. If Priority Status \= ESCALATED  
2. If Status \= ESCALATED, claim those first  
3. If Rank \= 10+, prioritize after escalated cases  
4. Oldest created case (FIFO \- First In, First Out)  
   1. For Status \= BLOCKED, review Case Comment for responses   
      1. If response available, complete request  
      2. If no response, send follow-up message:  
         1. *Friendly bump\! Just checking in on my previous message—let me know if you have any updates or need any clarification. Thanks\!*

## **Claiming a Case**

1. To take ownership, check the boxes next to the cases you want to assign to yourself and select “Change Owner” at the top of the list.  
2. Once assigned, change the status to “In Progress”.

Note: If the requester becomes deactivated, you will receive this error:

![][image4]

In this case, change the requester to your name and proceed to resolve.

## **Updating Case Status**

* In Progress: Actively working on the case  
* Escalated: Waiting on guidance.  
* Blocked: Waiting on a response from the rep. Bump blocked cases with reps every other day with a friendly reminder. If the requester does not respond after one business day, add a comment: "*Friendly bump\! Just checking in on my previous message—let me know if you have any updates or need any clarification. Please note, we will close out this ticket if there are no responses within 7 days. Thanks*\!"  
* Closed: No further action required from Comm Ops. Select from:  
  * Completed: Issue resolved by Comm Ops.  
  * No Response from AO: No response or activity from the AO. Automatically close if no response after 7 days.  
  * Not Required Anymore: Issue cancelled or resolved by another team.  
  * Not Comm Ops Related: Incorrectly submitted case, no action required.  
    * **Enterprise**: *Hello\! The Comm Ops requests workflow is only for SMB support. Please continue to use the \#ask-lemonade channel for ENT DDMx Support.* 

      *For ENT contracting or nintex issues, please submit a ticket here: https://doordash.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/2136*

      *Thank you for your understanding. This case will now be closed.*

  * Other: Provide reasoning for closing the case.

## **Communicating with a Requester**

* If additional information is needed, submit a new “Case Comments” at the bottom of the page.  
  * Add updates, questions, or comments for the requester.

## **Adding Internal Notes to a Case**

1. Navigate to the "Notes and Attachments" tab.  
2. Under "Notes", select "New" to add notes. Use notes to track progress and add context for anyone reviewing the case. 

## **Closing Case**

Use this when you are ready to **close** a case that has been fully resolved and work is complete.

### **✅ Step-by-Step Closure Process**

1. **Set Status to**: Closed  
2. **Closed Category**: 

| Closed Category | Additional Text Box | Reason for Use |
| ----- | ----- | ----- |
| **Training / Self-Serve** | N/A | Used when reps submit a request that already has a documented **self-serve process** available. Helps track gaps in training or knowledge. |
| **Data Issue** | N/A | Used when Comm Ops resolves a **data discrepancy** (e.g., deck rank, account owner update, account setup correction). |
| **System Error / Bug** | Ticket link (if applicable) \- use existing JIRA\_Ticket\_\_c | Used when updates are needed due to a **system error, limitation, or bug**. Linking the Jira/ServiceNow ticket provides traceability. |
| **Hand-Off** | Required field to specify team/channel |  Used when Comm Ops must **redirect the request** to another team’s owned process (e.g., Sales Ops, Legal, Support). Ensures accountability and routing visibility. |
| **Compliance** | N/A | Used for assisting reps with valid **compliance-related requests** (e.g., policy adherence, regulatory requirements). |
| **Duplicate** | N/A | Used when the case is a **duplicate submission** and has already been addressed. |

3. **Set Sub-Status to**: Completed  
4. **Enter Story Points**

   * Assign **1 story point per completed action or scenario** within the case.

   * Each investigation or deep dive also counts as **1 story point**.

   * Use this to quantify effort, not just resolution.

5. **Fill in “Additional Case Comments”**  
* Clearly list each action taken using this format  
  1\. Deep Dive    
  2\. Core Contract Reparenting    
  3\. Store Association
